definition.value: A methylcatechol carrying a methyl substituent at position 3. It is a xenobiotic metabolite produced by some bacteria capable of degrading nitroaromatic compounds present in pesticide-contaminated soil samples.
The monophosphate ester obtained by condensation of phosphoric acid with the primary hydroxy group of pyridoxal.
A 1-(phosphoribosyl)imidazolecarboxamide that is acadesine in which the hydroxy group at the 5' position has been converted to its monophosphate derivative.
A one-carbon compound consisting of a methine group triple bonded to a nitrogen atom
